{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Thus, we know little about how to engage youth in the design of these models.",
    "We investigated how youth engage in designing small GLMs by building on the rich tradition in learning sciences and child-computer interaction of positioning young people as designers of applications.",
    "We conducted a workshop spanning five class sessions (each 90 minutes long) with 35 high school students (ages 14-15) in which they designed very small GLMs (between 30K-600K tokens), which we call babyGPTs, using the nanoGPT framework.",
    "In this class activity, we took a data-driven approach that glassboxes, or makes transparent, how data shapes model performance and blackboxes the role of learning algorithms in the ML pipeline (Morales-Navarro & Kafai, 2024).",
    "Building on research on ML data practices (Olari & Romeike, 2024) and ethical sensemaking (Landesman et al., 2024), we analyzed the students' design process, discussions, artifacts, and interviews, to address the following question: What data practices and ethical considerations did participants engage with in the construction process of their own GLMs?"
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In this class activity, we took a data-driven approach that glassboxes, or makes transparent, how data shapes model performance and blackboxes the role of learning algorithms in the ML pipeline (Morales-Navarro & Kafai, 2024).",
